# Python (CDP)

Applies to `scrapers/` and `muvstok-api/`. Platform standards: [.agent/standards/coding-standards.md](../../.agent/standards/coding-standards.md).

## Stack

- Python 3.12+
- FastAPI, Pydantic v2, async I/O where the service already uses it
- `uv` + `ruff` (line length 100) + `mypy` strict in muvstok-api

## Structure

- Routes thin → services → repositories/clients → DB / Redis / external APIs
- Validate at API boundaries with Pydantic models
- No shared Python packages between `scrapers/` and `muvstok-api/`

## Safety

- Never log or commit secrets, tokens, connection strings, or callback HMAC values
- Preserve `correlation_id` / `job_id` through logs and callbacks
- Run service gates before marking work done: `make -C scrapers test lint`, `make check-muvstok`
